    "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nThis PR builds on top of #6712 and adds two commits\r\n  - First one removes support for thread-granularity agent and kernel\r\n  - Second removes support for warp-granularity agent and kernel\r\n\r\nThis should reduce the number of lines changed significantly.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n<!-- Every PR should have a corresponding issue that describes and motivates the work done in the PR -->\r\nCloses #6783 \r\nCloses #8424\r\n\r\n  - extend `agent_segmented_scan` with ability to to consume multiple segments per block\r\n     - Introduce new agent template parameter `MaxSegmentsPerBlock` which controls the size of `OffsetT` array in shared memory dedicated to storing inclusive-scan of segment sizes. The actual number of segments to process is passed dynamically to `consume_ranges` method. It can not exceed `MaxSegmentsPerBlock`, however.\r\n     - Multiple-segments are processed by reconstructing head-flags while loading values using `multi_segment_iterator` class, which is read- and write- transform iterator.  \r\n        - Read transformation reconstructs head-flag and forms value-flag pair, used as `AccumT` by `BlockScan`, and  \r\n        - write-transform unpacks value-flag pair and only writes the value to the output iterator.\r\n     - Mapping from `element_id` to `segment_id` and `relative_offset` (or rank) is encapsulated into searcher types.\r\n     - Three searcher types are implemented:\r\n        - When segment sizes are all the same, `segment_id = element_id / segment_size`.\r\n        - Generically, binary search in the array of inclusive-scan of segment sizes is performed. Two implementations (types) are provided:\r\n           - When static bound on array size of known (as it is in our case), branch-less binary search provides best performance\r\n           - When this bound is unknown, `cuda::std::upper_bound` can be used for larger number of sizes, and linear search using dynamic for-loop for  smaller sizes\r\n     - While computing inclusive-scan of segment sizes, we check if all sizes to be processed by block are the same, and use fixed-size searcher, otherwise use branch-less generic searcher.\r\n     - When dynamic number of segments equals 1, simpler `consume_range` call is made, which does not reconstruct head-flags \r\n\r\n   - Dispatch layer is modified to take 2 additional parameters (with default values), the number of segments to be processed by a worker (defaults to 1), and the type of worker requested (defaults to block).",
    "created_at": "2026-04-22T21:32:44Z",
    "updated_at": "2026-04-28T16:25:18Z",
